!                WHO SAID THIS?                 !
!                 Backend Docs                  !
=-----------------------------------------------=

This backend app was built with Python and served
using UV environments.

Tech Stack

 - Python
 - FastAPI
 - Uvicorn
 - WebSockets
 - Pydantic

-------------------------------------------------

This project combines the use of regular APIs,
WebSockets, and models to implement the system.

It is important to say that this version is intended
to work only as a single server.

-------------------------------------------------

Project Setup

Sync dependencies
 > uv sync

Run development server
 > uv run uvicorn main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

The APIs will be available at: http://localhost:8000

-------------------------------------------------

Project Structure

   src/
    ├─ who/
        ├─ room/          -> The code for room party control (including WebSockets)
        ├─ whatsapp/      -> The specific implementation of a reader in a WhatsApp context
        ├─ models.py      -> The concrete models used in the backend
        ├─ protocols.py   -> The concrete protocols used in the backend
        └─ main.py        -> The main app with the APIs